description: "that" (as conjunction). Note that this tag in C7 subsumed both “that” as a complementizer and “that” as a relativizer
after-determiner or post-determiner capable of pronominal function (e.g. "such", "former", "same")
before determiner or pre-determiner capable of pronominal function ("all", "half")
wh-determiner, functioning as relative pronoun, genitive ("whose")
wh-determiner, interrogative ("which", "what"). Note that this tag in C7 subsumed both interrog and relativizing uses
wh-determiner, interrogative, genitive ("whose"). Note that this tag in C7 subsumed both interrog and relativizing uses
general preposition (GL: Probably includes "to" but so what?)
catenative adjective ("able", as in "be able to")
genitive cardinal number, neutral for number ("two’s", "100’s")
singular locative noun, in naming expression (e.g. "Island", as in "Coney Island", "Street" in "Argyle Street")
plural locative noun (e.g."Islands", as in "Virgin Islands")
unit of measurement, neutral for number (e.g. "in", "cc")
objective wh-pronoun, interrogative ("whom")"). Note that this tag in C7 subsumed both interrog and relativizing uses
subjective wh-pronoun, interrogative ("who"). Note that this tag in C7 subsumed both interrog and relativizing uses
prep. adv., catenative ("about" in "be about to")
base form of verb "BE" (auxiliary), imperative or subjunctive. Note that for this and subsequent tags the insertion of an -A- in second position marks auxiliary use
base form of "BE" (lexical vb), imperative or subjunctive
base form of verb "DO" (auxiliary), indicative, imperative or subjunctive (GL: this annoyingly collapses imperatives in, which should be VB in PTB)
base form of verb "DO" (lexical), indicative, imperative or subjunctive (GL: also collapses imperatives)
base form of "HAVE" (auxiliary), indicative, imperative or subjunctive (GL: collapses imperatives (VB in PTB))
base form of verb "HAVE" (lexical), indicative, imperative or subjunctive (GL: Also collapses imperative)
base form of lexical verb (e.g. "give", "work") Note: excludes BE, HAVE and DO (see above, tags beginning VVB-, VVH-, VVD-)
-ing participle of lexical verb (e.g. "giving", "working") Note: excludes BE, HAVE and DO
infinitive (e.g. "to give..." "It will work...") Note: excludes BE, HAVE and DO
past participle of lexical verb (e.g. "given", "worked") Note: excludes BE, HAVE and DO
past participle catenative (e.g. "bound" in "be bound to")
-s form of lexical verb (e.g. "gives", "works") Note: excludes BE, HAVE and DO
